         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. His duties prevented Z. from answering Rovigo's last
                            letter. He wrote a letter to for R. Yedidiah Zarfati to transport it to
                            Rovigo. Zarfati who has left his home to gather funds to ransom his
                            friends and has credentials from the rabbis of Constantinople and
                            Saloniki. 2. Ζ. plans to immigrate to the Holy Land and seeks to
                            establish a yeshivah. He is looking all over Italy for benefactors to
                            support this idea. The yeshivah would be called 'Yeshivat Italyah' and
                            follow the example of R. Eliezer Shalom and R. Shabbetai Beer - but
                            these two rabbis failed to establish studious successors who would
                            continue their work. He asks Rovigo's advice if he shall write to his
                            community its entirety or notify individuals of his plans. Benjamin
                            ha-Kohen intends to join Z. in Erets Israel together with his wife and
                            mother. </note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">קוצר שעת הכושר ומקרי</note>
